A hike through a national park and a war game board, unlikely sources for a tremendously popular science fiction novel.

06:43.020 --> 06:46.540
The novel is Midnight at the Well of Souls. The author is Jack Chalker.

06:46.540 --> 06:51.660
The book concerns the Well World, an artificial planet constructed by a vanished civilization.

06:52.280 --> 07:00.840
The Well World is divided into 1560 separate environments, separate worlds really, each with its own climate, geography and intelligent inhabitants.

07:01.440 --> 07:05.260
Each division is shaped like a hexagon and for that reason they're called hexes.

07:05.920 --> 07:12.900
Chalker was in an isolated village called Stahikin on the shore of Lake Chelan in Central Washington State when he got the idea for the Well World.

07:14.400 --> 07:18.700
I got sitting by the lake that night and talking with some people.

07:19.740 --> 07:29.700
And I got the idea for this large world built by a long dead race and so on.

07:29.820 --> 07:32.280
And I didn't really have much of an idea of what it was.

07:33.080 --> 07:38.140
And they do have a service out of Stahikin that'll take you up to Trailhead.

07:39.180 --> 07:42.740
And so I went up to Trailhead and I wound up walking down.

07:42.980 --> 07:46.060
I'm a great hiker as long as the direction is down.

07:47.960 --> 07:52.620
I'm afraid I've never been to the bottom of the Grand Canyon because I can get down there but I can't get back up.

07:53.480 --> 07:59.860
But here was a trail that Taylor made for me. It was down the Cascades, all the way.

08:01.020 --> 08:08.400
So I took it and it took about eight and a half hours to walk the whole distance.

08:11.060 --> 08:13.900
And during that time you go through eight climates.

08:14.460 --> 08:18.120
You start off in the snow, you wind up in a rainforest.

08:19.660 --> 08:22.140
And some of the changes are rather abrupt.

08:22.360 --> 08:27.320
You just go around a switchback and it just changes from one climate to another.

08:27.320 --> 08:32.780
Each with its own different plants and insects and occasional mammals.

08:33.520 --> 08:35.320
Even the birds seem to be different.

08:35.580 --> 08:38.080
And I thought, yeah, this is how that big world would be like.

08:39.300 --> 08:43.680
So even though while I was on my way down I was kind of scribbling ideas.

08:45.800 --> 08:56.320
And I got the idea for this giant world composed of basically world-like different abrupt geography, climate, landforms.

08:56.320 --> 08:59.560
You name it, each with its own dominant race.

09:02.380 --> 09:09.360
By the time I hit bottom my head had pretty well worked out although I didn't really know what the shape of the things were going to be.

09:10.720 --> 09:14.060
Back home in Maryland he got some help on the shape of the well world.

09:15.380 --> 09:20.840
I was discussing the idea with a science fiction fan named Ben Yellow, some of that.

09:20.840 --> 09:21.480
No bellwitter.

09:22.900 --> 09:23.540
Rosalina.

09:24.300 --> 09:27.840
And he says, why don't you just use an Avalon Hill game board?

09:29.620 --> 09:31.220
And I thought, yeah, that would work.

09:31.820 --> 09:38.940
So we got out an Avalon Hill map, a war game map and a little trusty calculator.

09:39.760 --> 09:45.600
We laid a grid of these hexagons around a roughly earth-sized world.

09:46.260 --> 09:48.760
Of course you cannot cover a sphere with hexagons.

09:49.180 --> 09:55.680
So that means we had the north zone and the south zone, which would be the embassy's entry and exit point.

09:56.900 --> 09:58.320
That would cover our sphere.

09:59.380 --> 10:05.060
And then it was just simply a matter of sitting down and listing what was required to do.

10:05.960 --> 10:12.620
What kind of creatures and land, climate and so on I would have to do for the route of the story.

10:13.660 --> 10:21.980
Dropping by Avalon Hill, which I lived very near at the time, picking up some blank maps and just working it out from there.

10:23.440 --> 10:27.940
What Chalker worked out turned into his best known novel, Midnight at the Well of Souls.

10:28.540 --> 10:32.400
It was so popular that it went out of print a few months after its initial press run.

10:32.720 --> 10:36.820
And Chalker has added four novels since then, making a five book series in the well world.

10:36.820 --> 10:42.960
The whole thing turned out to be a colorful and exciting epic on the origin of the universe and all of the creatures in it.

10:43.380 --> 10:45.680
It should fascinate any reader of science fiction.

